Let’s bake, babies! 🧁

Baking has been used in drag for years! It’s a bullet-proof method for getting your makeup to last a looooooong time! ⏰

So, what is baking? 😍
Baking is a technique that includes applying a heavy amount of translucent powder under the eyes or areas where you think you crease the fastest 😇

So, what is actually happening? 

Once you allow the powder to sit for a while, during this time the heat from your face will allow your makeup to “bake” and it will set your foundation OR concealer, while the excess powder absorbs any oil! 😍 HOW COOL! 

Baking doesn’t suit everybody! But you should give it a shot and see if it works for you! 
It definitely works for me! 😍

I honestly can’t do my makeup without it 👀😅

*You cannot bake with compact powders* you have to use a loose powder for this to actually work. 

You can use ‘banana powders’ or ‘Translucent setting powders’ for this
- Maybelline fit me - Light 15 (my fav)
- Laura Mercier 
- Kay beauty loose powder 
- Makeup revolution banana powder 
- PAC HD powder 

I hope you Bake away!!! 😁

👄 POUTY Lipssss!!! 
Here we come!!! 👄😍

GURL, You neeeed to add lip liners into your lip routine! 👀
Your lip game is about to change!
😍😍😍

If you’ve never tried a lip liner, THIS video is a sign that you should! 😜😅

Pro tips 🚨
1. Preferably choose a cool toned brown color - it’s my PERSONAL favorite!!! 😉
2. OVER-LINE your Cupid’s bow and bottom center lip ONLY 
3. Trace the sides of your lip normally 
(DO NOT “overline” the sides ❌)
4. And MAGIC! in 5 seconds you’ve got Pouty lips! 👄

Basic colors of lip liners you need to own 
- Mauve / Rose colors ✅
- Cool & Warm Browns ✅
- Reds ✅
- Wines ✅

The Lip liner I’ve used in this video is from @ilmakiage x @carlibel - Luna (not available here)
